      "id": "P_WHEN_RSTB_IS_BELOW_VTH_CLEAR",
      "observable_contract": "When `rstb` is below `vth`, clear both PFD states and hold both outputs low. While `rstb` is high, a rising crossing of `ref` asserts `up`, and a rising crossing of `fb` asserts `down`. Once both states have occurred, schedule a reset after `reset_delay` and clear both states at that timer event. The reset input must also clear a pending one-sided UP or DOWN state even if the opposite edge has not arrived.",
